3.text: Fit the bump key into the lock-up to the last pin.

4.text: Slam and turn the bump key.

5.text: Pick a lock with a tension pick set.

8.text: Insert the pick above the wrench.

9.text: Open interior doors with a hex wrench.

10.text: Find or purchase a set of hex wrenches.

11.text: Fit the long end of a hex wrench into the hole on the door handle.

12.text: Turn the wrench to open the door.

13.text: Open a simple lock with a credit card.

14.text: Put the credit card into the side of the door.

15.text: Slowly but firmly pull the card towards you while turning the handle.

17.text: Unravel and straighten the coat hanger.

18.text: Lift the weather stripping from the bottom of the driver's-side window.

19.text: Scrape the hanger around and feel for a latch.

22.text: Bust stubborn doors with a battering ram.
